<TEXT>
a jury ordered a psychiatrist to pay nearly 
19 million to a female patient with whom he had sex numerous times 
over a 12year period billing her for each visit 
the multnomah county circuit court jury deliberated for five 
hours thursday before reaching its verdict against dr james l 
petroske of portland 
the woman a 55yearold former elementary school teacher was 
awarded 832000 in general damages for pain and suffering 1 
million in punitive damages and 43800 in lost wages 
testimony and evidence presented during the twoweek trial 
indicated petroske began treating the woman in 1967 and started 
having sexual relations with her in 1975 
james huegli the womans attorney said petroske ended the 
sexual relations in early 1987 while he was being investigated by 
the state board of medical examiners about allegations that he was 
having sex with another patient 
petroske admitted he lied to the state board about the number of 
patients with whom he had sexual relations in early july the board 
suspended him from practice for 90 days fined him 5000 and placed 
him on probation for 10 years 
petroskes attorney carol a hewitt told jurors during closing 
arguments that her client is not going to be practicing medicine 
under any circumstances after this case is over 
hewitt admitted petroske had inflicted physical damage on the 
patient but she contended it was not permanent huegli however 
said other doctors thought the woman suffered permanent brain damage 
from what he called a long insidious poisoning regimen of 
drugs prescribed by petroske 
huegli said petroski billed the woman for all her visits 
including the ones in which they engaged in sex 
</TEXT>
