<TEXT>
a chicagobound united airlines jet with 311 
people on board dumped fuel over the pacific ocean and returned for 
a safe landing friday after it developed engine trouble 
united flight 108 reported problems with the dc10s rear engine 
shortly after takeoff from los angeles international airport said 
federal aviation administration spokeswoman barbara abel 
frightened passengers who disembarked from the disabled plane 
told of hearing two loud bangs shortly after takeoff 
after dumping fuel over the ocean the pilot landed the plane 
about 220 pm pst faa investigators were checking the engine and 
there was no immediate determination of what caused the trouble 
the plane has three engines and is designed to be able to fly 
even if two out of three are disabled 
