<TEXT>
under pressure from congress the farmers home 
administration is easing some of the paperwork requirements for 
delinquent borrowers but it says a 45day deadline for responding 
to overdue notices wont change 
a growing number of lawmakers have been urging the agriculture 
department agency to extend the deadline which gives farmers 45 
days in which to respond after receiving official notices to begin 
settling overdue loan accounts 
the notices were sent out last month to more than 80000 
delinquent borrowers who owe fmha more than 8 billion 
theres just no way legally we can stretch it the deadline 
acting agency administrator la verne ausman said friday we must 
hear from the farmer within that time 
several basic response forms must be completed and returned 
within 45 days as the minimum requirement 
ausman said that in order to ease paperwork requirements for late 
repayers fmha county offices will accept supporting documents for 
the applications after the 45day deadline but that such agreements 
must be worked out with those offices 
the notices were sent out to fmha borrowers who were at least 180 
days delinquent in repaying loans the notices informed them of loan 
servicing and restructuring options and said failure to respond 
would trigger acceleration of loan collection a step toward 
foreclosure or forced sale of assets 
we have advised our field offices to use a test of 
reasonableness with borrowers who through no fault of their own 
are unable to complete all the forms on time ausman said 
for example he added if because of illness or other 
circumstances beyond his or her control a farmer couldnt obtain 
all the information he or she needed we wont be hardnosed if they 
have given us completed response forms and farm and home plans but 
we will be looking for evidence of a goodfaith effort on the part 
of the borrower to get all the forms in a timely manner 
ausman said that as a minimum the documents that must be sent in 
within 45 days include 
form fmha 4101 application for fmha services 
form fmha 4312 farm and home plan including the balance sheet 
attachment 2 acknowledgement of notice of program availability 
or attachment 4 response to notice informing me of fmhas intent to 
accelerate my loan 
</TEXT>
