<TEXT>
john gonella a former aide to president lyndon 
johnson and capitol hill lobbyist died friday at his maryland home 
at age 71 
gonella most recently an assistant to the vice president of the 
association of american railroads began his career in washington in 
1949 when he moved here to work as an information officer for the 
embassy of pakistan 
he was a press spokesman and congressional liaison with a number 
of firms before joining the state departments congressional 
relations office in 1965 he joined the johnson white house staff in 
1966 and served as a congressional liaison through 1969 
gonella worked as a washington consultant for two years and then 
worked from 197177 on the staffs of sens robert c byrd of west 
virginia and harrison a williams of new jersey 
during the 1950s gonella also wrote a golf column for the 
washington post 
gonella a native of dollar scotland graduated from glasgow 
university with degrees in economics and political science he 
served in the british army during world war ii and came to new york 
in 1948 where he was a professional golfer and radio and television 
newsman before moving to washington a year later 
</TEXT>
