<TEXT>
for 56 years betty sedat and grace 
dutton have been exchanging christmas cards or rather one 
christmas card sent back and forth year after year 
the greeting features a bagpipeplaying scotsman with the verse 
hoot for a jolly christmas ill send a card to wish ye a 
christmas full of cheer ill send my name in pencil so yell use 
the card next year 
mrs sedat first sent the card to her friend in 1932 
i thought it was funny she said so i did sign it in 
pencil along with the date mailed it off to grace and forgot all 
about it 
sure enough a year later it returned with ms duttons name 
signed below mrs sedats 
we signed and dated it every year in pencil of course first 
on the front then on the back until we ran out of room mrs 
sedat said 
the exchange continued even after mrs sedat moved to guatemala 
with her husband to do missionary work for several years with the 
nazarene church 
the friends say their relationship has been as durable as the 
card 
we keep in touch and see each other several times a year 
said mrs sedat 
</TEXT>
