bickering between nicaragua and 
honduras is threatening a summit planned for next month by central 
american leaders anxious to end the civil wars and hostilities in 
the region 
the latest stumbling block comes from the international court of 
justice at the hague netherlands the world court agreed this week 
to hear nicaraguas claims that honduras has been harboring and 
supporting usbacked rebels known as contras who are fighting 
nicaraguas leftist government 
honduran foreign minister carlos lopez contreras said wednesday 
the world courts decision threatens the future of negotiated 
settlements to the regions problems he said the courts move is 
politically charged and sets a judicial precedent totally 
incompatible with peace negotiations 
in addition president jose azcona hoyo of honduras has 
threatened to boycott regional peace talks unless nicaragua drops 
its world court case 
lopez and the foreign ministers of nicaragua el salvador 
guatemala and costa rica met earlier this month in mexico there 
they agreed that heads of state would convene in january in an 
effort to breathe new life into the stalled august 1987 peace plan 
the plan sets threemonth deadlines for ceasefires in el 
salvador nicaragua and guatemala 
it also mandates that governments of all five nations enact 
political amnesties and democratic freedoms and reconcile with 
political opposition groups it calls for an end to outside aid for 
rebel insurgencies and a ban on the use of one countrys territory 
to destabilize another 
the peace proposal was written by president oscar arias of costa 
rica who was awarded the 1987 nobel peace prize for his effort 
honduras says antigovernment nicaraguan rebels and refugees camp 
exist on honduran territory because of a lack of democratic freedoms 
in nicaragua 
for reasons of national security honduras doesnt want the 
contras lopez said nor do we desire the presence of more than 
60000 refugees from guatemala el salvador and nicaragua 
however lopez said honduras cannot eject the contras because 
we would be accused of being responsible for massacres and 
violating human rights 
lopez denounced what he called the sandinista practice of using 
international organizations to pressure other nations 
but nicaragua hailed the courts decision and nicaraguan 
president daniel ortega said honduras should accept it 
the same court ruled in nicaraguas favor in 1986 in a suit 
against us support of the contras the united states has refused 
to recognize the courts jurisdiction in the area 
as the main judicial organ of the united nations the court has 
no enforcement powers 
the arias plan sought to end the honduran problem as well as long 
wars in nicaragua el salvador and guatemala but the heady days 
following the 1987 signing later turned to disappointment and 
frustration 
the four us allies in central america el salvador honduras 
costa rica and guatemala blame nicaragua and its largest backer 
the soviet union for the persistent turmoil nicaragua says the 
united states is trying to militarize the region and find a pretext 
to invade nicaragua 
