syria which supports amal last month withdrew 66 truce 
observers from the highlands east of sidon that raised fears of 
major clashes but so far only localized skirmishes have occurred 
the new pact provides for a disengagement of forces and the 
removal of frontline barricades to enforce a ceasefire between amal 
and the plo around sidon provincial capital of south lebanon 
the conflict has centered on the city and its environs since 
arafats fighters were driven out of their strongholds in beiruts 
refugee camps by rival syrianbacked palestinian factions in july 
something amal had failed to do 
