120000 applicants were selected for government employment a report 
said today 
the examination in september was reminiscent of the system used 
in imperial china where civil servants also were selected through 
tests 
in presentday china however the functions of communist party 
and government officials often overlap and political connections 
frequently play a role in obtaining jobs and promotions 
last year communist party chief zhao ziyang proposed a civil 
service system suggesting government employees not engaged in 
political work should obtain jobs on the basis of an examination 
and wages and promotions should depend on merit 
the idea of giving priority to seniority and other wornout 
concepts that stifle peoples initiative and creativity should be 
eradicated he said 
the guangdong examination was a prelude to the civil service 
system said the independent ming pao newspaper quoting the 
progovernment china news service 
the examination was adminstered to 120000 people in an open 
fair and competitive manner the report said 
about 11000 applicants passed the examination including 
workers high school and university graduates and 3000 people from 
rural areas the report said it did not give a breakdown of 
participants by age or sex 
the new employees will work in provincial departments including 
security courts finance and revenue the report said 
