women are in a firstfloor showerlocker room area that is lined 
walltowall with cots and metal bunk beds piled high with blankets 
and clothes the children play down the center aisle with donated 
toys a fake undecorated christmas tree and a television are on a 
corner table 
donated food and clothing also has been evenly split with a 
varying number of miamis homeless population who are staying in 
another part of the stadium 
but while the goods have poured in and volunteers are abundant 
housing for the refugees remains a critical issue already the 
refugee population has outgrown an empty cityowned building being 
renovated as a shelter the stadium must be emptied by midjanuary 
and the new shelter can only accommodate 150 people ms garcia said 
other alternatives being discussed include setting up a trailer 
park on three acres of stateowned land in west dade 
despite the problems mayor xavier suarez says he hasnt become 
overly worried about the citys ability to absorb the latest wave of 
refugees 
were obviously rolling with the punches here he said 
this is a pretty resilient community 
